# ECC Cross-Harness Conventions (ADR-0119)

The repo is wired into the `affaan-m/everything-claude-code` bundle to
keep Cursor, Claude Code, Codex, Gemini, and Copilot aligned on:

1. **Generated-code policy** — every agent edit must leave a
   machine-readable trail (commit prefix, ADR reference, or a
   `tools/ai/hooks/` preflight log). AgentShield CI rejects PRs that
   mutate files outside the session manifest.
2. **Pre-edit guards** — before editing shaders (`shaders/**/*.hlsl`),
   run `tools/lint/check_shader_registration.py`. Before touching
   `engine/core/crypto/`, run the constant-time audit script.
3. **Multi-harness commands** — when a task says *"run X across
   harnesses"*, dispatch via the ECC `ccg-workflow` commands rather
   than invoking each harness by hand.
4. **Hook budget** — Cursor hooks under `.cursor/hooks/` must complete
   in ≤ 250 ms on an RX 580 dev box. Slower checks belong in
   `agentshield.yml`, not in the pre-prompt path.

Full install flow lives in `tools/ai/README.md`. Third-party payload
is vendored read-only under `third_party/everything-claude-code/`; do
not patch upstream files in-place — wrap them in
`.cursor/hooks/*.wrapper.*` scripts instead.
